# Quarkus Backend Rules

## Layer Rules (apply to all Java files)

- `*Entity` classes live only in `data/entity/` — never referenced from `api/` or `service/`.
- Services inject `*Repository` port interfaces, never `*PanacheRepository` directly.
- REST resources call services only — no business logic, no Panache calls.
- All constructor injection — never `@Inject` on fields.
- `@Transactional` only on service methods, never on resource methods.

## REST Resource Pattern

```java
@Path("/api/v1/{entities}")
@Tag(name = "{Entities}")
public class {Entity}Resource {
    private final {Entity}Service service;

    {Entity}Resource({Entity}Service service) {
        this.service = service;
    }

    @POST
    @ResponseStatus(201)
    public Response create(@Valid Create{Entity}Request request) {
        var dto = service.create(request);
        return Response.created(URI.create("/api/v1/{entities}/" + dto.id())).entity(dto).build();
    }
}
```

## Service Pattern

```java
@ApplicationScoped
public class {Entity}Service {
    @Transactional                          // write ops — always
    public {Entity}Dto create(...) { ... }

    public {Entity}Dto findById(Long id) { // read ops — no TX
        return repository.findById(id)
            .orElseThrow(() -> new {Entity}NotFoundException(id));
    }
}
```

## Naming Table

| Concept | Suffix | Example |
|---------|--------|---------|
| REST Resource | `Resource` | `NominaResource` |
| Service | `Service` | `NominaService` |
| Domain Model | (none) | `Nomina` |
| Panache Entity | `Entity` | `NominaEntity` |
| Port Interface | `Repository` | `NominaRepository` |
| Port Impl | `PanacheRepository` | `NominaPanacheRepository` |
| ACL Translator | `AclTranslator` | `NominaAclTranslator` |
| MapStruct Mapper | `Mapper` | `NominaMapper` |
